  id: Cervicoscutular_muscle.L
  partName: Cervicoscutular muscle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left cervicoscutular muscle Left is a superficial cutaneous muscle located
    in the cervical region of the canine body. It extends between the neck and skin
    structures surrounding the ear and shoulder area. This muscle primarily functions
    to move and tense the skin during facial, neck, and shoulder movements.
  - It contributes to subtle skin adjustments that aid communication, protective
    reflexes, and response to external stimuli such as insects or touch. Although
    relatively thin, the cervicoscutular muscle participates in coordinated muscular
    actions involving nearby superficial muscles. Proper function helps maintain
    skin mobility and flexibility.
